Resize an image to a fixed size while maintaining the aspect ratio

`convert file.jpg -resize 800x -background white -gravity center -extent 800x600 file-aspect.jpg`

This will pad above/below or to the right/left side of the image with
the colour specified as `-background`, resize the image to the width or height
as supplied to `-resize` and force the image to be the size supplied to
`-extent`.
